color":"text-light","styles":{"self":{"textAlign":"center","fontWeight":400}}},"subtitle":"Join us in the Yunnan highlands for an unforgettable eco-experience.","colors":"bg-dark-fg-light","styles":{"self":{"justifyContent":"center","padding":["pt-16","pb-16"]}},"actions":[{"type":"Button","label":"Explore Our Ecotours","altText":"View our ecotour offerings","url":"/ecotours","showIcon":false,"icon":"arrowRight","iconPosition":"right","style":"primary","elementId":"","__metadata":{"modelName":"Button"}}],"__metadata":{"modelName":"GenericSection"}},{"type":"GenericSection","title":{"type":"TitleBlock","text":"Cloud Mountain","color":"text-dark","__metadata":{"modelName":"TitleBlock"}},"subtitle":"Your Sustainable Travel Companion","text":"We are dedicated to providing exceptional travel experiences that support local communities and sustainable development in some of the most vulnerable areas of Yunnan province, China.\n","actions":[{"type":"Button","label":"About Us","url":"/why-us","icon":"arrowRight","iconPosition":"right","style":"secondary","__metadata":{"modelName":"Button"}}],"media":{"type":"ImageBlock","url":"/images/blog/iscovering-naxi-culinary-traditions/About Us Banner OPT.webp","altText":"Cloud Mountain Ecotours and Nature Education","__metadata":{"modelName":"ImageBlock"}},"badge":{"type":"Badge","label":"About Us","color":"text-primary","__metadata":{"modelName":"Badge"}},"colors":"bg-light-fg-dark","styles":{"self":{"alignItems":"center","flexDirection":"row-reverse","padding":["pt-8","pb-8","pl-2","pr-2"],"justifyContent":"center"}},"__metadata":{"modelName":"GenericSection"}}],"markdown_content":"Exploring the unique food culture of Lijiang's Naxi people, from traditional markets to cooking with local families.\n\n![Traditional Naxi ingredients at the market](/images/tours/wild-heart-of-lijiang/highlight-2.webp)\n\n## The Heart of Naxi Cuisine\n\nThe Naxi people of Lijiang have developed a rich culinary tradition over centuries, blending ingredients from the surrounding mountains with techniques passed down through generations. At the heart of their cuisine is the principle of harmony - balancing flavors, textures, and nutritional benefits in every dish.\n\n![Local family preparing traditional meal](/images/FW-Icon5.jpg)\n\n## Learning at the Source\n\nOur food tours take you beyond restaurants and into the homes of local families, where you'll learn to prepare dishes using fresh ingredients from the morning markets. From hand-pulled noodles to medicinal herb soups, each recipe tells a story of the land and people.\n\n![Fresh ingredients from Lijiang market](/images/tours/lijiang-old-town/highlight-6.webp)\n\n## A Journey of Flavors\n\nThe journey through Naxi cuisine is also a journey through the seasons. Spring brings wild mushrooms from the forests, summer offers fresh river fish, autumn delivers丰收 of vegetables, and winter features hearty root vegetables and preserved meats.\n\n![Traditional Naxi restaurant in Old Town](/images/tours/wild-heart-of-lijiang/highlight-9.webp)\n\n## Bringing It Home\n\nMany travelers leave Yunnan with not just memories, but new skills. Our cooking classes include detailed recipe cards and guidance on sourcing authentic ingredients back home, so the flavors of Lijiang can continue to enrich your table.\n"},"site":{"favicon":"/images/shared/brand/cm-logo-color.png","footer":{"logo":{"url":"/images/shared/brand/cm-logo-footer.webp","altText":"Logo light","type":"ImageBlock","__metadata":{"modelName":"ImageBlock"}},"text":"","primaryLinks":{"type":"FooterLinksGroup","title":"","links":[{"label":"EcoTours","altText":"Ecotours page","url":"/ecotours","icon":"arrowRight","iconPosition":"right","style":"secondary","type":"Link","__metadata":{"modelName":"Link"}},{"type":"Link","label":"Why Us","altText":"","url":"/why-us","showIcon":false,"icon":"arrowRight","iconPosition":"right","style":"secondary","elementId":"","__metadata":{"modelName":"Link"}},{"type":"Link","label":"Partner W